# Language

Semantic primes, schemas, intelligence architecture, music coordinates.


## Schemas = Bond Patterns = Innate Seed

16 bond patterns (2^4) map 1:1 to Lakoff/Mandler image schemas — the
pre-verbal concepts humans are born with:

  identity=IDENTITY, π=FORCE, ∘=PATH, π+∘=TRAVERSAL, ∮=CYCLE,
  π+∮=FULL-EMPTY, π+δ=CONTACT, ∘+∮+δ=BALANCE, π+∘+∮+δ=CONTAINER

An infant experiences FORCE (womb), CYCLE (heartbeat), FULL-EMPTY
(hunger), CONTACT (touch), CONTAINER (own body) — all before language.
~24 schemas reduce to 16 irreducible patterns (extras are magnitude
variants, compositions, or inverses).


## Three-Layer Seed

  Layer 0: bonds/schemas (16, innate, hardcoded, never changes)
  Layer 1: primes/first words (65 NSM, learned year 1, anchored to schemas)
  Layer 2: full vocabulary (memetic, context-learned, infinite)

Same as generations: Gen1=values, Gen2=operations, Gen3=patterns.
The equation already has the seed. The intelligence doesn't need a
separate "model" — the equation IS the model.


## Structural Rules

Parts of speech = dominant dimension:
  noun=μ, verb=τ, adj=φ, adverb=φ+τ, preposition=χ, pronoun=μ+φ

  Antonyms = sign flip in 1-2 dimensions
  Synonyms = distance ≤2 in 4D Euclidean space
  Tense = T magnitude (past=+2, present=+1, future=-2)
  Intensity = higher magnitude, same signs (warm→hot = Q+1→Q+2)
  Metaphors = cross-domain coordinate match
  Questions = unknown dimension set to 0
  Negation = Q flip

Validated: independent derivation test (Grok derived 4/5 exact from
rules alone). Status: BEST GUESS. Structural rules more robust than
individual prime→coordinate mappings.


## Reversed LLM

Traditional: compress data into weights (140GB), GPU decompresses.
Ours: keep data born-indexed on disk, evaluate coordinates in real time.
Storage high, compute low. "Model" = equation + density map (4D histogram).
One pass, no training. Character encoding directly affects index quality.


## Music = Coordinate Walks

Music maps to (τ,χ,μ,φ): τ=tempo, χ=pitch register, μ=dynamics, φ=tonality.
Genre coordinates match cultural perception:

  Hard rock (+2,+1,+2,+1) = "powerful" = same as festival EDM
  Pop (+1,+1,+1,+1) = hylo = the attractor
  Punk vs reggae = antimatter (max distance, cultural opposites)
  Death metal = aggressive rap = industrial (all +2,-1,+2,-1)

12-bar blues = narrative walk (stay→move→return→tension→resolve).
Music therapy = coordinate walking (ISO principle). Ravel's Bolero =
pure μ walk. Silence = origin. Key changes = coordinate shifts.

Caveat: genre coordinates assigned qualitatively, not measured from
audio features. Predictions involving spectral analysis would strengthen.


## Language IS Therapy

Sentences are coordinate walks. Therapeutic language walks toward
target coordinates. "Take out your stress on the punching bag" — three
+D words, sentence walks OUTWARD, the physical therapy has the same
coordinates. The sentence IS the therapy.


## Bond Relationships in Language

16 bond patterns = 16 linguistic relationship types:

  0  identity        self-reference / same word
  1  π reference     one word points to another (pronoun → noun)
  2  ∘ invocation    verb calls its arguments
  4  ∮ continuation  sequential / list linkage
  8  δ evaluation    adjective evaluates noun
  3  π∘ traversal    subject traverses to object
  5  π∮ accumulation list items building toward total
  6  ∘∮ iteration    repeated action
  9  πδ selection    filtering / choosing
  10 ∘δ conditional  if-then relationship
  12 ∮δ search       scanning / looking
  7  π∘∮ reduction   summary / totaling
  11 π∘δ transform   change of type
  13 π∮δ progressive gradual change
  14 ∘∮δ causation   because / therefore
  15 π∘∮δ pipeline   complex multi-step reasoning

Transformers use 8-16 attention heads per layer — learning imperfectly
from data what the lattice provides exactly from geometry. Morpheme
transforms (affixes as coordinate deltas) in build/morphemes.


## ~20 Convergence

Lattice bonds (16), RISC ISAs (~20), Wierzbicka primes (~20), Lakoff
schemas (24), primitive recursive (6 combinators). Four domains converge
at the same floor. This is the dimensionality of a complete system.
